replies.commentText:
@Eli Parker

This is not about self-improvement. It is about controlling language in order to thereby control how people think and perceive the world. The progressive left, and indeed any institutionalized power, has always and will always do this. E.g., look at how they changed the way in which illegal immigrants are talked about. They shift the narrative from speaking about illegals in pejorative terms, i.e., as "illegals", to a completely neutral term, i.e., "undocumented".

Anyway, in my opinion, the fact that we have the luxury of worrying about 'gendered language' says all that needs to be about the state of current public discourse.
